Sedgwick Group Plc &lt;SDWK.L> said itswholly-owned Canadian subsidiary Sedgwick Tomenson Inc hadacquired BSi Incorp for a maximum eight mln Canadian dlrs.    The funds will be raised through the issue of up to 1.16mln ordinary Sedgwick shares to the vendors of BSi by no laterthan 31 January 1991. Some 427,054 shares already have beenissued.    BSi is a privately-held Canadian company involved inactuarial, employee and executive benefits consulting andadministration. Its 1986 pretax profits excluding extraordinaryitems totalled 1.14 mln Canadian dlrs. Reuter&#3;